## Setup & Installation

Clone the repository:

```sh
git clone <your-repo-url>
```

Navigate to the project directory:

```sh
cd MovieSearchApplication/
```

Install the dependencies:

```sh
npm install
```

Start the development server:

```sh
npm run dev
```

After running `npm run dev`, open your browser and navigate to the localhost URL shown in the terminal to view the application.

## Core Concepts

### State Management

Uses Redux Toolkit for global state management.
The main slice is `moviesSlice`, which manages:
- Movie list
- Movie details
- Loading/error states
- Favorites (with localStorage persistence)

### API Integration

All API requests use Axios.
The base URL and API logic are defined in `src/services/omdbApi.js`.

### Routing

Uses React Router for navigation.
Main routes are defined in `App.jsx`:
- `/` — Movie search and results
- `/movie/:id` — Movie details

### Styling

Uses Tailwind CSS for utility-first styling.
Custom colors and fonts are defined in `tailwind.config.js` and `App.css`.

## Key Components & Files

- `src/App.jsx`: Main app component, sets up routes
- `src/pages/SearchPage.jsx`: Displays the movie grid, search bar, and filters
- `src/pages/DetailsPage.jsx`: Shows detailed info for a selected movie
- `src/components/MovieCard.jsx`: Card UI for each movie
- `src/components/SearchBar.jsx`: Search input for movies
- `src/components/TypeDropdown.jsx`: Dropdown for movie type filter
- `src/components/Pagination.jsx`: Pagination controls
- `src/slices/moviesSlice.js`: Redux slice for movies and favorites
- `src/store/index.js`: Redux store configuration
- `src/services/omdbApi.js`: API logic

## Extending the App

- **Add More Filters:** Extend `TypeDropdown` or add new filters for year, genre, etc.
- **User Authentication:** Integrate authentication to allow users to save favorites to their account.
- **UI Enhancements:** Add animations, dark mode, or more detailed movie views.
- **Testing:** Add unit and integration tests for components and Redux logic.

## Technologies Used

- React
- React Hooks
- Redux Toolkit
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- OMDb API for movie data
- Vite (for fast development and build)

## License

This project is for educational and demonstration purposes only.

